Strange.....every leakdown test I have ever down is always with the piston at
TDC. Sun used to supply a whistle so you could rotate the engine to TDC and
the whistle would toot. It was a bear holding it at TDC. As you applied air,
it would push the piston down if you were a tad before or after.

